<bug>
	<id>18205</id>
	<title>Docker 1.9 --build-arg not working</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">My machines lay behind a firewall and I tried to set up a build proxy like this:</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">```</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">docker build \</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.4">--build-arg https_proxy=$HTTP_PROXY --build-arg http_proxy=$HTTP_PROXY</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.5">--build-arg HTTP_PROXY=$HTTP_PROXY --build-arg HTTPS_PROXY=$HTTP_PROXY -t test .</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.6">```</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.7">and when I run this command it will first try to pull the ubuntu images, and then failed for network timed out.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">I used tcpdump to capture all packages during that and I didn't find any package whose destination is the proxy server ip, so I figured that probably because the proxy settings in the command are not working.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
